# AI News Digest — Implementation Plan

Add a daily automated AI news digest to the WhatsApp group bot. Every morning at 08:00 (configurable timezone), the bot fetches AI-related stories from Hacker News, summarises them with Gemini Flash 2.5, and posts a formatted digest. Users can also trigger an immediate digest via `/news`.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **`NEWS_CHAT_IDS`** — You must add a new env var containing the comma-separated WhatsApp group JIDs that should receive the automated daily digest. Example: `NEWS_CHAT_IDS="120363xxxxxxx@g.us,120363yyyyyyy@g.us"`. Without this, the scheduled digest won't know which groups to post to. The `/news` command always replies to whichever chat it was sent in, no extra config needed.

> [!NOTE]
> The seen-article cache is **in-memory only** (not persisted to DB). It resets on bot restart. This keeps the implementation simple — on a fresh start the bot may re-surface articles from the previous day, but will deduplicate within the same runtime session. We can persist to DB in a follow-up if desired.

---

## Proposed Changes

### New Service Layer

#### [NEW] [NewsService.ts](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/service/NewsService.ts)

Responsible for fetching and filtering HN stories.

- Calls `https://hacker-news.firebaseio.com/v0/topstories.json` to get top story IDs (first 30)
- For each ID calls `https://hacker-news.firebaseio.com/v0/item/{id}.json` to get the story object
- Filters by title using the keyword list from §7.3:
  `AI, LLM, GPT, Claude, Gemini, OpenAI, Anthropic, machine learning, neural, model, agent, artificial intelligence, DeepSeek, Mistral`  
  (case-insensitive, word-boundary match)
- Returns up to 8 filtered candidates with `{ title, url, id }`
- Maintains an in-memory `Set<string>` of seen article URLs; skips any URL already seen; trims to last 100

#### [NEW] [NewsDigestService.ts](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/service/NewsDigestService.ts)

Responsible for AI summarisation and formatting.

- Accepts the ≤8 candidate articles from `NewsService`
- Builds a Gemini prompt instructing Gemini Flash 2.5 to:
  - Select 3–5 most important stories
  - Write a 2–3 sentence summary per story
  - Append a one-liner "Thought of the day" about AI
- Uses `@google/generative-ai` (already installed) — same `GEMINI_API_KEY` / `GEMINI_MODEL` env vars
- Returns a pre-formatted WhatsApp markdown string matching the example output (bold `*`, italic `_`, emojis, numbered list, `🔗` links)
- Returns `null` if Gemini call fails (caller skips silently)

---

### New Scheduler

#### [NEW] [NewsScheduler.ts](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/sheduler/NewsScheduler.ts)

Follows the exact same pattern as [TaskScheduler.ts](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/sheduler/TaskScheduler.ts).

- Singleton export `newsScheduler`
- [setWhatsappService(service)](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/sheduler/ReminderScheduler.ts#10-17) function — called from [app.ts](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/app.ts) after bot starts
- [start()](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/sheduler/TaskScheduler.ts#34-48) — schedules a `node-schedule` cron job at **08:00** daily using `DEFAULT_TIMEZONE`
- [stop()](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/sheduler/TaskScheduler.ts#49-67) — cancels the cron job
- Internal `runDigest()`:
  1. Calls `NewsService.fetchAiStories()` → candidates
  2. If no candidates → log + skip (no message to group)
  3. Calls `NewsDigestService.generateDigest(candidates)` → formatted message string
  4. If generation fails → log + skip (no message to group)
  5. Sends formatted message to each JID in `NEWS_CHAT_IDS` via `whatsappService.sendMessage()`
- [sendManualDigest(chatId)](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/sheduler/TaskScheduler.ts#322-332) — public method called by `NewsCommand`; same pipeline but sends to one specific chat

---

### New Command

#### [NEW] [NewsCommand.ts](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/commands/NewsCommand.ts)

Follows the same pattern as [TaskDigestCommand.ts](file:///d:/dev/thegaminghub/wa-group-reminder/src/commands/TaskDigestCommand.ts).

```ts
export class NewsCommand implements Command {
  name = "news";
  aliases = ["/news"];

  async execute(context: MessageContext, services: ServiceContainer): Promise<void> {
    const { newsScheduler } = await import("../sheduler/NewsScheduler.js");
    await newsScheduler.sendManualDigest(context.chatId);
  }
}
```

- If no new articles are available (digest pipeline returns nothing), sends a configurable fallback:  
  `_No new AI stories available right now. Try again later!_ 🤖`

