## Verification Plan

> [!NOTE]
> No automated tests exist in this project. Verification is fully manual.

### Manual Verification

1. **On-demand `/news` command**
   - Start the bot locally: `npm run dev` (or `node dist/app.js` after `npm run build`)
   - In the WhatsApp group, send: `/news`
   - Expected: bot replies with a formatted AI digest (3–5 stories + Thought of the day)
   - Check terminal logs for: `[info] Fetched X HN stories`, `[info] AI news digest sent to <chatId>`

2. **Deduplication (seen-article cache)**
   - Send `/news` a second time in the same session
   - Expected: digest either shows different articles OR if all have been seen, bot replies with the fallback message  
     `_No new AI stories available right now. Try again later!_ 🤖`
   - Check logs for `[info] Skipping seen article: <url>`

3. **Error handling (no message posted to group)**
   - Temporarily set `GEMINI_API_KEY` to an invalid value, send `/news`
   - Expected: bot does **not** post anything to the group; error is logged only
   - Restore the API key afterwards

4. **Scheduled automated digest**
   - Temporarily change the schedule hour in `NewsScheduler.ts` to 1 minute from now (e.g., `rule.hour = currentHour; rule.minute = currentMinute + 1`)
   - Restart the bot and wait ~1 minute
   - Expected: digest is automatically posted to each JID in `NEWS_CHAT_IDS`
   - Revert the schedule change after verification
